{"tid":2120018,"cid":33,"subCid":0,"title":"BNO移民政策正式出爐！！！！！","createTime":"2020-07-22T12:02:50.000Z","updateTime":"2020-07-25T18:55:36.000Z","uid":285843,"like":18,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":32,"replies":[{"pid":"b6a7761269709bdcb0b1f2d64d87b0e53731766f","tid":2120018,"uid":285843,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-07-22T12:02:50.000Z","msg":"The UK will create a new immigration route for&nbsp;British National (Overseas) (BN(O)) citizens&nbsp;and their dependants.<br />\nThis page will be updated with the latest information about this immigration route.<br />\n<br />\nNew immigration route for BN(O) citizens<br />\n<br />\nThe UK will open a &lsquo;Hong Kong BN(O) Visa&rsquo; for BN(O) citizens and their close family members from January 2021.<br />\nYou&rsquo;ll be able to apply for this route from outside or inside the UK.<br />\nYou&rsquo;ll be able to apply to enter or remain in the UK for an initial period of 30 months, extendable by a further 30 months, or a single period of 5 years. You&rsquo;ll be able to work and study but you won&rsquo;t be able to access public funds such as social welfare benefits.<br />\nYou&rsquo;ll be able to apply to settle in the UK (also called &lsquo;indefinite leave to remain&rsquo;) once you&rsquo;ve lived here for 5 years. After 12 months with this status you can apply for British citizenship.<br />\nTo be eligible for this visa route you&rsquo;ll need to show that you:<br />\n<br />\nhave BN(O) status &ndash; you don&rsquo;t need valid BN(O) passport to show this and you don&rsquo;t need to request a new passport if it&rsquo;s expired or has been lost<br />\n<br />\nnormally live in Hong Kong<br />\n<br />\ncan accommodate and support yourself financially in the UK for at least 6 months<br />\n<br />\nshow a commitment to learn English, where appropriate<br />\n<br />\nget a&nbsp;tuberculosis (TB) test certificate&nbsp;from a clinic approved by the Home Office<br />\n<br />\npay a fee and the&nbsp;immigration health surcharge<br />\n<br />\nRead the&nbsp;Hong Kong BN(O) settlement visa policy statement&nbsp;for more information on these arrangements.<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/hong-kong-bno-visa-policy-statement\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gov.uk%2Fgovernment%2Fpublications%2Fhong-kong-bno-visa-policy-statement&d=DosFxDX7yTzXLN9Gri3QgFCKRJWvDXkpEFRbHtszOvM%3D&h=de22daf3\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/hong-kong-bno-visa-policy-statement</a>"},{"pid":"6194434e79d43a821c2c1320e27f57f972ee47fb","tid":2120018,"uid":151196,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-07-22T12:04:09.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/lick.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/lick.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/lick.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"a7b15dbe790275adc4a3d4824344684f7986e102","tid":2120018,"uid":9681,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-07-22T12:04:50.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/bomb.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/bomb.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/bomb.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/bomb.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"3bd9c28dabb373c266783ede74437368aec95afa","tid":2120018,"uid":331173,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-07-22T12:06:25.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"5629c7c473732103717e514bb63bdd464a1e6fe4","tid":2120018,"uid":291865,"like":1,"dislike":1,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-07-22T12:06:31.000Z","msg":"from January 2021 仲有少少時間"},{"pid":"bec6d019a0dba6e66bf656adf4ec370d8de8611e","tid":2120018,"uid":219635,"like":0,"dislike":10,"score":-10,"citedBy":3,"r